ith successful implementations, trials and errors, and the continuous relentless effort to miniaturize computers promise the emergence of viable applications, wearable technology has reached billions of people across the globe.<\/p>\n<p>Before we look ahead on the list of apps involving wearable technology, here is how you can classify it into various segments:<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Detailed_classification_of_wearable_devices\"><\/span>Detailed classification of wearable devices<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full pdimgauto wp-image-6783\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/Detailed-classification-of-wearable-devices.png\" alt=\"Detailed classification of wearable devices\" width=\"724\" height=\"601\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/Detailed-classification-of-wearable-devices.png 724w, https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/Detailed-classification-of-wearable-devices-300x249.png 300w, https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/Detailed-classification-of-wearable-devices-600x498.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 724px) 100vw, 724px\" \/><\/p>\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\">Source:- <a href=\"https:\/\/www.mdpi.com\/1996-1073\/11\/3\/547\/pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MDPI<\/a><\/h6>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Most_promising_and_prominent_wearable_app_for_iPhone_and_Android\"><\/span>Most promising and prominent wearable app for iPhone and Android.<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\n<li>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Citymapper\"><\/span><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.citymapper.app.release&amp;hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Citymapper<\/a><\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Citymapper, a supremely useful app, acts as a refreshing guide in its own league for Android Wear users. The application brings live information to your wrist-watch while you are having a stroll through a new town or wish to get the status on your public transport at home.<\/p>\n<p>The application is built in a way where it updates you about real-time bus, taxi, train and ferry data and offers you the best route possible. It also has turn-by-turn navigation that gives an estimate on walking or cycling times along with Uber status to make sure you reach the destination in the quickest time possible.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Calm\"><\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/us\/app\/calm\/id571800810\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Calm<\/a><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>This is one of the top rated apps on both iOS and Android platforms for a sound sleep and relaxed meditation. Calm app has a refreshing feel. The app with its meditation lessons facilitates Android and Apple smartwatch users with a daily meditation routine.<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"ParKing_Where_is_my_car\"><\/span><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=il.talent.parking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ParKing: Where is my car?<\/a><\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Keep forgetting where you parked? Asking yourself where is my car? Where did I park? Find my car?<\/p>\n<p>With ParKing, the KING of parking, it will never happen again! This simple car locator app is exactly the solution you need to locate your vehicle!<\/p>\n<p><strong>Key features:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\n<li><strong>One Click Parking<\/strong> &#8211; Save a new parking reminder on a map with just one click.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Parking History<\/strong> &#8211; History of your previous parking places.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Automatic Parking<\/strong> &#8211; Automatic parking detection using your car&#8217;s Bluetooth device.<\/li>\n<li><strong>User Defined Zones<\/strong> &#8211; User defined zones with no automatic parking notifications (e.g. home, office).<\/li>\n<li><strong>Parking Time Reminder \/ Parking Timer<\/strong> &#8211; Parking time reminder to avoid fines.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Navigation<\/strong> &#8211; Multiple navigation options to your car.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Indoor \/ Underground Parking<\/strong> &#8211; Add a photo or a text note to your parking for indoor\/underground parking places. No GPS is required!<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1Password\"><\/span><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/gb\/app\/1password-password-manager-and-secure-wallet\/id568903335\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">1Password<\/a><\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>When it comes to wearable apps, Less is more.And the stripped-back version of 1Password&#8217;s iPhone app is one such example. This app covers login keys for two-factor authentication. It is simple but handy<\/p>\n<p><strong>Key features:<br \/>\n<\/strong>It helps you create strong, unique passwords and memorizable pass-phrases for all your online accounts.<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\n<li>The app will automatically fill usernames, passwords, credit card numbers and addresses into websites, as well as the supported apps<\/li>\n<li>You can access your information on all your mobile devices and computers.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<h3